rule("——————————————— ︾ Giga Parkour Editor BETA rev 8.3 ︾ ————————————————")
{
	event
	{
		Ongoing - Global;
	}

	conditions
	{
		"Inspired by Peace (T6QQT) & Taw's (G361B) editors for Mercy Parkours!\nFeatures:\n> Supports importing maps from Peace/Taw editors\n> Readable controls for Consoles\n> Multiplayer editing\n> Better performance\n> Planning to support all heroes!"
		disabled True == True;
		"Beta Rev 8 (2024-Sep-18):\n- Added rule to auto-restart lobby\n- Added export map instructions\n- Improved bhop detection\n- Fixed ghost cp bug when editing last level\n- Fixed free mode being disabled on last level\n- Fixed ability exploit when touching checkpo"
		disabled True == True;
		"Beta Rev 7 (2024-Sep-13):\n- Added subroutine to save player progress, allow for continuing where you left off\n- Fixed bug when importing scoreboard colors from Peace\n- Fixed some Edit hud issues\n- Added Taw's CheckpointInstructionTexts\n- Fixed bug with sec"
		disabled True == True;
		"Beta Rev 6 (2024-Sep-09):\n- Added icons to StartingAbilities menu\n- Reworked hero ability detection rules"
		disabled True == True;
		"Beta Rev 5 (2024-Sep-07):\n- Implemented final compression algorithm\n- Added clash gamemode\n- Added Free Walking\n- Fixed Scoreboard duplication issue\n- Added more orange options"
		disabled True == True;
		"Beta Rev 4 (2024-May-04):\n- Added palette wheel \"Options\" & \"Tools\" menus\n- Reworked controls for controller accesibility"
		disabled True == True;
		"Beta Rev 3 (2024-Apr-06):\n- Added Palette wheel menu\n- Added debugging options to orange settings"
		disabled True == True;
		"Beta Rev 2 (2024-Mar-15):\n- Optimized conditions that checked for un-pressed buttons\n- Reordered the normal and Edit Mode HUD\n- Removed Herobrine"
		disabled True == True;
		"Beta Rev 1 (2024-Mar-08):\n- Added beams when moving objects for easier location\n- Fixed some broken edit menus"
		disabled True == True;
		"Work on this editor began in Aug-2023 :)"
		disabled True == True;
	}

	actions
	{
		"How to import maps from Peace (T6QQT) and Taw's (X98FK, G361B):\n1. Open your original map code\n2. Take a note or photo of your workshop settings (Orange options)"
		disabled End;
		"== PEACE's ONLY ==\n3. Open the workshop and copy the topmost 8 rules:\n  \"Put the data here\"\n  \"Creator and code\"\n  \"HUD guidance text\"\n  \"Map guidance text\"\n  \"Big message text\"\n  \"Small message text\"\n  \"Player title\"\n  \"Personalized configuration\""
		disabled End;
		"== TAW's ONLY ==\n3. Copy these 6 rules at the top:\n \"Checkpoint Definitions...\"\n \"Configuration\"\n \"Checkpoint Hint Text\"\n \"Checkpoint Instruction Text\"\n \"Checkpoint Floating In-World Text\"\n \"VIPs\"\n\n DONT COPY \"Workshop Setting Definitions\""
		disabled End;
		"4. Open Giga Editor and navigate to the workshop\n5. Select all rules with \"SELECT ALL\" button\n6. With all rules selected, click the \"PASTE RULE\" button, then click on \"MOVE UP\" once\n7. Your original map's rules should now be at the top"
		disabled End;
		"8. Enable your map\n9. Configure these options in orange settings:\n- CP Radius (Taws)\n- Orb Radius (Both editors. Peace radius is between 0.5 and 1)\n- Land on ground (Peace)\n- Bot Gravity (Peace)\n- P.Ability restrictions (Taws)"
		disabled End;
		"If you have questions or have any issues to report you can find me in:\ndiscord.gg\\mercyparkour"
		disabled End;
		"Parkour Editor by GigaMercy"
		Global.VIPs[Count Of(Global.VIPs)] = Array(Custom String("GigaMercy"), Custom String("{0}GigaMercy", Ability Icon String(Hero(
			Mercy), Button(Ability 1))), Custom Color(251, 134, 28, 224));
		"Special Thanks!!"
		Modify Global Variable(VIPs, Append To Array, Array(Array(Custom String("Aeternalys"), Custom String("{0}Aeternalys",
			Ability Icon String(Hero(D.Va), Button(Ultimate))), Custom Color(64, 224, 208, 224)), Array(Custom String("maylanix"),
			Custom String("{0} maylanix", Icon String(Skull)), Custom Color(255, 153, 187, 255)), Array(Custom String("poobie"),
			Custom String("{0} poobie", Ability Icon String(Hero(Mercy), Button(Jump))), Custom Color(102, 120, 255, 255))));
	}
}

